g.text: 1. A process opens a file and calls read().
2. asset-fuse sends a Fetch request to the remote cache with metadata from the manifest.
3. The remote cache downloads the requested data from the internet if needed. The blob is now stored remotely, indexed by the digest.
4. The remote cache returns the digest, which asset-fuse can use to download file chunks from the remote cache as needed.
5. asset-fuse copies parts of the file into the read buffer and returns.
